{%- comment -%}
  date-lt — formats a date the Lithuanian editorial way. Month names and the
  patterns come from locales (general.months_genitive, general.date_md,
  general.month_periods, general.date_coarse), so the English site renders
  correctly from the same call. Used for the pre-order expected date
  (preorder-status, PDP note/track, cart line).

  Two granularities:
    exact  (default)      → „rugpjūčio 28 d."  /  "August 28"
    coarse (coarse: true) → „rugsėjo viduryje" /  "mid September" — the picked
      day maps to a third of the month (1–10 pradžioje · 11–20 viduryje ·
      21–31 pabaigoje). Used while Būsena = Gamyboje, so a product still in
      production never promises a false-precision date.

  Params:
    date   (date)    required — a date object or ISO string the date filter accepts.
    coarse (boolean) optional — month + beginning/middle/end instead of the exact day.

  Usage (capture — render output has surrounding whitespace stripped):
    {%- capture eta -%}{% render 'date-lt', date: d, coarse: true %}{%- endcapture -%}
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if date != blank -%}
  {%- assign m_idx = date | date: '%-m' | plus: 0 | minus: 1 -%}
  {%- assign months = 'general.months_genitive' | t | split: '|' -%}
  {%- if coarse -%}
    {%- assign day_n = date | date: '%-d' | plus: 0 -%}
    {%- assign periods = 'general.month_periods' | t | split: '|' -%}
    {%- if day_n <= 10 -%}{%- assign p = periods[0] -%}
    {%- elsif day_n <= 20 -%}{%- assign p = periods[1] -%}
    {%- else -%}{%- assign p = periods[2] -%}{%- endif -%}
    {{- 'general.date_coarse' | t: month: months[m_idx], period: p -}}
  {%- else -%}
    {%- assign day = date | date: '%-d' -%}
    {{- 'general.date_md' | t: month: months[m_idx], day: day -}}
  {%- endif -%}
{%- endif -%}
